==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ave Mary
<hw>A"ve Ma"ry</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>. }</mhw> <ety>[From the first words of the Roman Catholic
prayer to the Virgin Mary; L. <ets>ave</ets> hail, <ets>Maria</ets>
Mary.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A salutation and prayer to the Virgin
Mary, as mother of God; -- used in the Roman Catholic church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To number <qex>Ave Maries</qex> on his beads.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A particular time (as in Italy, at the ringing of
the bells about half an hour after sunset, and also at early dawn), when
the people repeat the Ave Maria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Ave Maria</qex> ! blessed be the hour !</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Avena</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
